  "id" : "7976070",
  "contents" : "\"Fathers' Day (1997 film)\"\nFathers' Day (1997 film) Fathers' Day is a 1997 comedy film directed by Ivan Reitman and starring Robin Williams, Billy Crystal, Julia Louis-Dreyfus, and Nastassja Kinski. It is a remake of the 1983 French film \"\"Les Compères\"\". In the film, Collette Andrews (Kinski) enlists two former lovers, cynical lawyer Jack Lawrence (Crystal) and lonely, ex-hippie, suicidal writer Dale Putley (Williams) to help her search for her runaway teenage son Scott by telling each man that he is the father. When Jack and Dale run into each other and find out what's happening, they work together to find Scott and determine"
} {
  "id" : "8876963",
  "contents" : "\"Harald the Old\"\nHarald the Old Harald Valdarsson, also known as Harald the Old (, born circa 568) appears only by name in \"\"Hversu Noregr byggðist\"\", but his father, sons and their descendants played a central role in the politics of Scandinavian legends. \"\"Hversu Noregr byggðist\"\" tells that he was the son of Valdar, who was the son of Hróarr (i.e. king Hroðgar of \"\"Beowulf\"\"), and Harald was the father of Halfdan the Valiant and the grandfather of Ivar Vidfamne. \"\"Skjöldunga saga\"\" tells that the same Valdar (i.e. Harald's father) disputed that Rörek, the cousin of Hróarr (Hroðgar) should succeed Hrólfr Kraki (Hroðulf)"
}

