} {
  "id" : "14017173",
  "contents" : "\"William Tonks\"\nWilliam Tonks William Tonks is a musician based out of Athens, Georgia. He is most known as a dobro player, song writer, and singer. Tonks was raised in Montclair, New Jersey before moving south to Savannah, Georgia at the age of nine. His sister gave him his first guitar in Savannah, which he learned to play the instrument on. His inspiration to play the guitar came from watching the Beatles movie \"\"Help!\"\". He began to take classical guitar lessons in Savannah, but towards the end of lessons he would work on rock songs with his teacher. Later on, in college,"
} {
  "id" : "4173950",
  "contents" : "\"Matthias Röhr\"\nbegan playing the guitar at age twelve. Despite his strict education and his youth, Röhr discovered what was important in his life. The repetitive church visits and the ministers, who always tried to make him a better man, were not parts of the life he wanted, but the music was. He and his friends pooled their money to pay for guitar lessons. After a few weeks he left the lessons, because he wanted to play \"\"real\"\" music and not folk music or endless scales. Soon after, he sold his guitar, bought an electric bass guitar and joined a school band."
}

