  "contents" : "\"Isaiah Williams\"\nposition by sophomore Darrius Heyward-Bey. Williams was moved to Z receiver where he shared playing time with redshirt freshman LaQuan Williams. Wide receivers coach Bryan Bossard said, \"\"Isaiah Williams is more talented than Darrius Heyward-Bey ... I've told him that; I've told Darrius that—talking about God-given ability, running, catching the ball, speed, height. Darrius just outworks him, and that's why he's had all the success he's had.\"\" That year, Williams played in all 13 games, including six starts and recorded 395 receiving yards to finish second on the team. In 2008, Williams again played in 13 games with six starts."
}

